Challenge: Refactor a Slideshow Component

03

In this final challenge of the workshop, your goal is to make the CampSpots slideshow component fully accessible.

Draw upon the lessons and examples from throughout the workshop as you work toward the following goals.

Update slideshow controls to use focusable and operable elements.

The user should be able to use the keyboard to advance through slides one at a time with the arrow icons on the sides of the slides, or by clicking a dot at the bottom of the slides.

Add ARIA labels to each button in the slideshow.

Write descriptive messages about the function of each icon button.

Implement keyboard support

A keyboard user should be able to change slides with the Arrow keys and exit fullscreen mode with the Escape key.

Implement focus management

When the user exits fullscreen mode, keyboard focus should return to where it was: the button that launches fullscreen. Set up the slideshow container with a tabindex value of -1 to allow it to receive focus via scripting on open. Use a React ref for the fullscreen button.

Add a Live Region

Update the slideshow container to support live region announcements so the content will be read as it cycles through the images.

Conditionally apply an ARIA Role

Different ARIA roles should be applied based on which mode the user has selected, so application mode will only apply to fullscreen mode.

Update image semantics by marking them up as figures

Images with alt descriptions are important, but from a structure perspective it’s nice to be more semantic.

Convert the images in the slideshow to use the <figure> and <figcaption> elements.
